  "text": "RNAi activity at low MOI, as shown by luciferase reporter assay ( fig. 3 h) , whereas at high MOI RNAi activity was reduced to a level similar to that seen with artificial knockdown of Dicer, a key component of the RNAi pathway, ( fig. 1 c) . Importantly, analysis of noninfected A549 or Vero cells showed that transduction with rAd-GFP did not significantly affect the morphology or growth rate of the cells during the course of experiments. However, the reduced growth of Vero cells transduced at high MOI was observed 10 days after transduction (results not shown). Comparable results were obtained when Vero cells were infected with poliovirus (results not shown). Interestingly, similar observations were made by Kay and colleagues [CITATION_1] and Chen and colleagues [CITATION_2] , who showed that decreased expression of siRNAs reduced the toxic effects. Nontoxic doses of adenoviral vectors expressing shRNAs could be used therapeutically, and adenoviral shRNAmediated inhibition of expression of multidrug resistance protein 2 in a mouse model without detectable alteration of the cellular RNAi machinery was reported [CITATION_3] .",
